<h1>@KJ{{every}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @KJ{{every}} <em>unit of time</em>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@KJ{{every}} is a prefix used with a unit of time to mean "every".

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha@KJ{{every^year^one^degrees}}ha@KJ{{day^book}}he@KJ{{going}}ku.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I go to Japan at least once a year.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@KJ{{every}} can be used with nouns that imply a specific time.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{ji-nn}}ha@KJ{{every^meal}}@KT{{sarada}}wo@KJ{{eat}}beru.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Jean eats salad at every meal.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@KJ{{every}} cannot be used if the unit of time is preceded by a numeral. It is also used with words of
Japanese origin of one or two syllables.
</p>

